  <bulletin id="5" date="20160331">
    <title>China Twist</title>
    <sections>
      <section>
        <title>China: a new bubble risk</title>
        <chapter>
          <paragraph>The real estate markets in some of China’s major economic centers have again heated up, with extreme price increases in Shanghai, Shenzhen, Suzhou, and in some parts of Beijing. With government controlled purchasing restrictions looser than they have been in the past decade, many home buyers are jumping in fast, as though afraid “of missing the boat.”
          </paragraph>
        </chapter>
