      <section>
        <title>Down payments in China: the true story</title>
        <abstract>What is a down payment? An amount of money that you pay at the time that you buy something but is only a part of the total cost of that thing.30 local business in Shenzhen sold outstanding loans for home down payments of 2.5-3 billion Yuan.</abstract>
          <chapter>
            <paragraph>
              <list type="unordered">
                <item>A. how much normally homebuyers need to put down of a home’s value</item>
                <item>B. Chinese home buyers which have borrowed money to make home down payments</item>
                <item>C. some property developers cover 100% of a down payment, for who promises to pay back in one year</item>
                <item>D. new properties in Shanghai which offer a zero down payments</item>
              </list>
            </paragraph>
          </chapter>
