        <section>
          <title>China vs Us a flashback of 2008 subprime crisis</title>
          <chapter>
            <title>The begin of a bubble</title>
            <paragraph>Lenders pushed outsized home loans on people without the wherewithal to pay them back.When home prices fall, banks and investors holding the loans had to eat massive losses.</paragraph>
          </chapter>
          <chapter>
            <title>Like US</title>
            <paragraph>Chinese home buyers borrow money to pay for down payments.</paragraph>
          </chapter>
          <chapter>
            <title>Unlike US</title>
            <paragraph>International investors have not jumped into buy these loans.</paragraph>
          </chapter>
